 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unikatjef.showPublicProfile?language=EN>nikatjef</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#333333>(9/12/02 10:43:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=339.topic&index=51>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/nikatjef/Everquest/Rogue.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Some indication that level cap may be raised to 65</span><hr size=1> Greetings,<br>
<br>
   As I understand it, VI is going to add more levels, however, you will only have those levels while in PoP.   So for example, you could be Lvl 63 in PoP, but only 60 when you zone back to pre-PoP zones.   By doing it this way, the old content will remain stable, while new content can be added on top of it to make players even more powerful.   Further, if I understand correctly, the new spells that were seen on test, will be available to you while in PoP, but not in VT, or Ssra, etc.<br>
<br>
   My only real concerns are how they are going to track XP, and how will they upgrade skills.   The XP is a huge issue due to XP loss on death and AAXP.  For example, assume that you have maxed level in PoP, you go on a Coldain Ring War, and lose level 60 after 30 deaths, do you become level 59 in PoP, or do you simply lose part of one level in PoP.<br>
<br>
   Skills are another huge issue.  Currently, the system is hard coded with a cap on skills/stats of 255.  Well, how much harder will it be to cast a level 65 spell with a 255 casting skill?  Or does Uber Warrior01 suddenly lose 10K hp when he zones out of PoP because his STA drops from 400 to 255?<br>
