<br>
It is possible, but unlikely that levels stay while spells do not.<br>
It is likely that some specific spells may not function, at least initially, in some specific non-PoP zones where they might be abused, rather like <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> CotH</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is disabled in some zones.<br>
<br>
There may be some specific abilities that only function or make sense in PoP, for example there was some text about opening up an elemental portal, that might be a mage only port to an elemental planes.<br>
<br>
I predict that if any major advancement, level, spell or abilities, is genericly made not to function in non-PoP zones, that consumer outrage will bring a quick end to that, replaced with more particular prohibitions, similar to CotH disabling.<br>
